        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 7 at 2:00PM CDT until June 7 at 2:45PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 200 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Gorgas to 6 miles west of Bankhead Lock And Dam
to near Jena, moving southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Tuscaloosa, Northport, Holt, Lake View, Brookwood, Coaling, Vance,
Coker, Samantha, McFarland Mall, Lake Lurleen State Park, Tuscaloosa
Amphitheater, Tuscaloosa Regional Airport, Lake Wildwood, Boley
Springs, Mercedes Benz Of Alabama, Binion Creek Landing, Abernant,
Shelton State Community College, and Bryant Denny Stadium.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
